what if i got it wrong, and no poem or song, could put right what i got wrong?
I saw you there, since then everyday.  it's like I'm lost and thinking of you in every way.  since I fell into your eyes, all I know is that you get me high, you get me high.

talk about nostalgic

great 21st birthday, it was so nice having friends here.  it was the textbook 21st birthday (except for the pete part.)  it was painful when everyone left.

i love asheville,
i love unca,
i love my classes,
but it feels so fruitless.  something is missing.

i dont know.  i wish i had closer friends here.

i feel empty.

:(
Will you love me still when we awake and you find that the sanity has gone from my eyes?

i owe you all a major update.

but the most important news right now is:

AVETT BROTHER'S NEW CD TOMORROW!!!!

woo!!
i'm just trying not to drown.

believe it or not, i love taking care of these kids.  babysitting, youth-sitting, whatever you want to call it.

last night pete made dinner for us and we sat outside and ate strawberry shortcake and sang queen bohemian rhapsody (with no music to back us up) really loud.  it was priceless.

and then we worked on homework/projects.  i'm behind in my work from helping them.

and once again i saw them off to school this morning, made them breakfast, etc. (asked them questions like my mom does)

and now i'm back in bed waiting for the coffee to kick in so that i start my project.

i'm going to miss them when their parents come back.

but i won't miss living in a suitcase and plastic bags.
"you could make a movie about your life." ~eduardo

i'm getting more and more obsessive compulsive every day.

i blame my mother.
i have reverted back to across the wire.

"Dark clouds may hang on me sometimes 
But I'll work it out... "  ~dave

yeah, totally chickened out.

put in my two weeks notice with limited availability for those two weeks.

that gives me time to find a job though.

and i can kind of make my own schedule.

i think i'm going to quit my job today.
life is too short to be unhappy.

when it rains, it pours.  i guess.

i dont want to go to work.
or class.

i need a vacation.
ether bunny! yay!!! (by the way, i am adorable. if you haven't noticed)

its raining men.
hallelujah!
its raining men!
don't say its over- 'cause thats the worst news i could hear.
I don't want to be your other half.  I believe that one and one make two.

AVETT BROTHERS TONIGHT!!!

"i wish you'd see yourself as beautiful as i see you."

is it just here or is it nationwide?

wow.
too bad you're not here.
to hear me singing bad madonna songs.

alot of leaving here, arriving there, i'm tryin to go just about everywhere
alot of thinkin about where i'm goin' next.

i have an interview with the asheville daily planet today.
its a weekly newspaper.
the position is production assistant.
it would give me some paid experience.

i'm scared shitless.
i'm going to go see me some damien rice.

"In many ways I am a smog-breathing twentysomething, graduate arse of a stereotype.

But are there hidden depths beneath that surface?  Who knows?  When the woman in Pret gives me too much change, I tell her so.  When she gives me the right amount, I pop the coppers in the little metal charity tin that they hide underneath the chocolate bars.  I cry at a good film, send my mum a card on Mothering Sunday and enjoy suprising Lucy.  Underneath my cynical roving eye, I'm a sloppy, slushy romantic at heart.

If I return home early from work I give my tube Travelcard to a friendly smackhead so he can continue to pump cheap drugs into his damaged veins.  I work long hours and feel guilty about earning so much money.  I'd like to do some good in the world and I'd very much like to pack it all in and spend some time travelling on the east coast of Australia.

Lucy's right: I'm a tosspot."

~Iain Hollingshead

oh please just let me please break down.

it could be the best $.99 i've spent in a while

...he said girl you better try to have fun no matter what you do.  but he's a fool. cause nothing compares, nothing compares to you!!!

and snowing.
and it seems so appropriate.

a taste of the good life is over.

back to surviving on coffee and clove cigarettes.

Sorry about the every kiss. 
Every kiss you wasted back
I think the thing you said was true, 
I'm going to die alone and sad.

so,
what about how:

1.  noone updates their livejournals anymore.  i'm highly disappointed, yet i still check back daily for any updates.
2.  i am so far behind in school its ridiculous, yet i am still procrastinating.  it is pathetic.  and then i beat myself up for procrastinating, and REALLY don't get any work done.
3.  i'm working on a flash project of a kaleidoscope which is pretty fun
4.  i have a cool design project going on
5.  i'm extremely far behind in portuguese
6.  i need to do homework, but i'd rather sleep, so instead i'm updating my livejournal?
7.  i have these books for design class and i really want to read them but who has time for this kind of "recommended" reading.
8.  i have some pleasure reading i'm dying to do
9.  its like a wine cellar in my room
10.  its supposed to snow tonight
11.  i need to remember to give theresa her christmas present.
12.  i have every day carefully planned out until this weekend, of each homework assignment, laundry, etc that needs to get done.
13.  i have so much to do, i need to get off the internet!!

wow. i've cried so much in the past two days that it's embarrassing.
it all started last night when i went to work.  i was exhausted and i held it all in
when i was leaving work i made it to the staircase before i started crying
i came home and took a pain killer and felt ok
went to sleep
woke up this morning in pain
started crying over something stupid
took another pain killer
was ok
only got out of bed for lunch
stayed in bed the rest of the day
tried to call in sick to work
but the manager guilted me into coming for a few hours
i hung up the phone
started crying again

its not even the pain.  yes, it hurts. yes my jaw is really stiff and i can't really open my mouth.  and i can't eat.

but its more that i feel exhausted.  like i've been dragged along the sidewalk.  like i will start crying if someone looks at me the wrong way. because i'm just that tired.  and pathetic.  and i dont want to get out of bed.  because i dont feel up for facing the world.  because if i get crap from a guest about the new menu, chances are, i will start crying. at the table.  in their soup.

and the most upsetting thing for some reason, is that noone understands.  i didn't know it was going to be liek this.  i thought i'd be up and running in two days.  i didn't know i would be so emotional and feel so incredibly drained when i haven't done anything to begin with.  that i would WAKE UP feeling drained.  morgan says its the pain killers. and she would know.  anyways i feel like a baby, i feel like i'm overexaggerating, but how can i be overexaggerating when i'm crying, right?

anyways, i have to get out of bed because i have to go to work.

let me paint the picture:

theres probably 2 inches of snow on the ground
the show if falling hard

my mom is driving me crazy asking what she can do for me

ugh
i think i'm going to take another pain killer
my head really hurts
i wish i could play in the snow
i would be nothing without my friends.
"we accept the love we think we deserve." -perks of being a wallflower
i wish i had one of you to talk to...

went to the dentist today, have to get 2 wisdom teeth removed on feb. 1st.  i'm kinda nervous, and wondering how much time i need to request off for work.

in other news, i'm broke and the bills keep coming in (including dentists bills).  i'm so over this.

i had major nightmares last night

and my wisdom teeth hurt

:(

trip to savannah cut short.
house in cashiers got broken into.
mom and i will head up there first thing in the morning.
what a mess.

2006 in a Nut Shell:

-drank more, ate more, smoked more
-worked more, studied more
-became more of a workaholic?
-discovered i like wine
-became a better server
-worked hard in school
-made a cool animation
-got a house
-hiked a mountain with rosie
-kept in touch with friends (which i thought i could never do.)
-acquired life changing friendships
-learned to play hungarian uno
-read several books
-started to learn portuguese
-became stronger, more independant
-became closer to my family
-began to cherish family values more
-hopefully became more confident?
-switched schools
-moved cities
-explored asheville
-got an awesome job
-helped friends in time of need
-never really got depressed
-started drinking more coffee
-started smoking cloves on occasion
-started really dating
-hugged more
-didn't make any tragic mistakes

overall, a great year

"there's reason to believe maybe this year will be better than the last."  -counting crows

"Its not easy so, this,

But, you my dear, I tell you true enough

But fall aside this, 
stumbling down drunken roads
I find myself more and more mistaking
Myself for some one else..."  -dave

-high fidelity
